That could be a false assumption. There is no evidence of anything but crackle and pop. Nothing useful in the form of intelligent signal messages has been obtained. Rather disapointing after decades of waiting. I am not ridiculing the SETI program. I just think it should be expanded upon. More funding and bigger telescopes provided. It is an interesting topic though. I strongly believe we need better launch systems in order to put more numerous telescopes in space. Interferometry using hundreds of giant mirrors in space would be durn cool. Having the industry in place to access asteroid resources as building material would be very interesting. Our two movements want the same thing I guess. You want contact with Space and it all comes down to better space access. Thanks for editing the nematode AC. It must be a full moon or something.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=contraconstantius>contraconstantius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/3/03 6:38:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=651.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Are We Alone...? </span><hr size=1> SETI and other programs like it are searching for life in the past. Even a null signal could come from an intelligent race. If it takes hundreds of years to go from not releasing radio waves to releasing a lot, and millions of years for us to detect them, then there could be intelligent, radio emitting life only a few thousand light years away that isn't being picked up.<br>
<br>
The radio spike you mentioned could have been a first attempt at using radio. If it was in a few hundred years they could start using radio a lot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2850<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/8/03 6:08:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=651.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/nimoy.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: you are going to sleep</span><hr size=1> Radio signals are one way of trying to discern other intelligences out there but I personally would like to see some money spent on visual scanning. Lens telescopes have inherent size limitations but reflector mirrors don't. Not in space at any rate. Seeing pictures of clearly inhabited Alien Worlds circling distant suns would settle the question for me. I seriously doubt we are alone but if that turns out to be the case then the universe will be a lonely place to explore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=contraconstantius>contraconstantius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/03 9:14:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=651.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/nimoy.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: you are going to sleep</span><hr size=1> A lot of radio signals we use are &quot;crackle and pop.&quot; Who says intelligent life wouldn't encode their signals to sound random? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=prenda2@nuclearspace>prenda2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/03 11:48:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=651.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Are We Alone...? </span><hr size=1> <br>
